    public static enum DateParser.ImpreciseDatePreference
extends java.lang.Enum<DateParser.ImpreciseDatePreference>
    When a range or imprecise date value is found, what is the preference for handling it?

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      FAVOR_EARLIEST
      Return the earliest reasonable value for the interpreted date or range.
      FAVOR_LATEST
      Return the latest reasonable value for the interpreted date or range.
      FAVOR_MIDPOINT
      Return the midpoint between the earliest and latest possible values for the interpreted date or range.
      PRECISE
      Return as precise a date as possible.

      • PRECISE

        public static final DateParser.ImpreciseDatePreference PRECISE
        Return as precise a date as possible. For ranges and periods where more than one date is supplied (e.g., FROM 17 JUL 2016 TO 31 JUL 2016), use the first of the two dates.

      • FAVOR_MIDPOINT

        public static final DateParser.ImpreciseDatePreference FAVOR_MIDPOINT
        Return the midpoint between the earliest and latest possible values for the interpreted date or range. For example, if a value of "1900" is supplied, the value returned is 1900-07-01 (July 1, 1900). "JUL 1900" is supplied, the value returned is 1900-07-15 (July 15). If the supplied value is not a range (i.e., there is only one date), return as precise a value as possible.
